caption: I wish this parc will never be famous please. Haha this is one of my fave silent parc internet neighborhood in Paris to just enjoy my lunch and reading book.

This gem can be reached by deviating from Paris' high line trail, which IMHO is hands down a much more beautiful and immersing walk through forgotten corners of the city. Excellent spot for a picnic, short or longer stop and definitely if you're with kids.

The Reuilly - Paul Pernin Garden is a very nice park in Paris that is located along the pathway that goes from the petite ceinture to the edge of Paris. I highly recommend anyone who's looking for a nice quiet walk in Paris to take this path and rest and relax on these different parks like this one.
Lovely park in the heart of the 12th district with also an amusement Park for kids

Part of the Promenade Plantée, an old railtrack above the city ground level that gets one from Gare de Lyon radially to the Bois de Vincennes in the East outskirts. It features a remarkable collection of trees, bushes, plants and flowers very well preserved and a safe 1h walk without cars or traffic.
Stopped here on the walk along the high line. There’s a wee cafe and at the opposite side water fountains including sparking water.

Cool walk from Bastille square to somewhere else, on the tracks of an ancient railroad, first or second floor level. Different perspective on Paris. After some time we went back street level they have nice artisan stores under the rail way
Amazing suspended gardens with seats and flowers. Impressive sculptures too. Hard to believe you are at the heart of Paris. So tranquil and beautiful. A place to visit!

This was the first park I ever took my son to. He loved waddling around the grass and picking up leaves. He was watching a local school play rounders too. There was also a guy doing a bunch of stretches the whole time we were there. I don't know his story.  Five stars
It’s clean and well maintained, optimal for small informal gatherings.
Wonderful, almost forgotten park at the end of the Coulee Verte. Go for a walk and relax or picnic in the grass at the end.
Nice place to hangout in this garden.
Rubbish. The worst garden in Paris.  DON'T GO THERE.  (Do you think they'll believe me?)
Cute park at one end of Coulee Verte Rene-Dumont. There's a small duck pond near the sandwich shop and we saw a brood of ducklings! The bridge over the park is cool.

Wonderful little park.  Grassy area is awesome for picnics, especially if you have kids.  Do NOT miss the Italian-made sparkling water fountain, one of only a handful in Paris.  The promenade plantee is a pleasant and unique way to get here from the city center, if you have time for the walk from Bastille.
Really nice park with plenty of space, water fountain and lots of bins. There are benches and chess tables on the upper level.

Discovered this place while out for a Sunday stroll in January. Unfortunately the lawn was closed for the season, but we are looking forward to returning in the spring. Good playground for kiddos aged 2-12 nearby
Nice park in Coulée Verte. Sparkling water available in near fountain.
No dogs allowed. Not even with a leash.
Beautiful park

I am a foreigner who stayed in a friend's house right across the street from this park and in spite of the fact it is not close to the main touristic places in Paris I enjoyed being close to it.   It is a total different perspective from the city.   I encourage to have a picnic there one afternoon.  Obviously way before it gets dark.
One of my favorite places in Paris
Terrace gardens connecting the Coulée Verte Rene-Dumont to the street below
A good spot to tan during hot summer days
Nice park, great flowers!
Loved this place in Paris. It's a great start/end to a nice walk on top of an old viaduct. Truly something different in such a big and busy city.
So interesting architecture of the parc: stairs, decorated by beautiful flowers, play yard, picnic zone and one corner which is decorated for each Halloween, by very talented artist
Calm place
Absolutely stunning museum. Amazing experience for kids of all ages, from 2 to 99 :) highly recommended
I had a short walk there, for about 30-40 min. It was good but not really a must-see. But if you live around or your just passing by, it can be an option.
Really nice place, one of the last garden not overcrowded when the sun is shining.
Beautiful park, very clean and well kept, plenty of space for picnicking and for children to run around and play.
Great park for children and very artistic statues
An awsome place with a beautiful place to spend time  with your beloved ones or family or children. Simply wonderful and experience mental peace.
Beautiful garden , peaceful and wonderful to walk in
Quiet and not particularly crowded garden to spend relaxing time with family and kids.
Great walk and great garden. I wish green spaces across the world were implemented as creatively as this one.
Chill and have fun
